ef=\"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/?page_id=784\">Acutignathidae<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/?page_id=788\">Angulognathidae<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/?page_id=792\">Concavigulidae<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/?page_id=1532\">Kamptoconidae<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/?page_id=1715\">Odontotrochidae<\/a>, and the\u00a0<a href=\"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/?page_id=1155\">Spinosacculidae<\/a>,<\/p>\n<p>Our global-outreach division is also hoping to acquire specimens from Russia, China, and the continents of South America, Africa and Antarctica.<\/p>\n<p>The fields of synthetic taxonomy are ever-expanding, thanks in large part to the planet-wide network of tireless and entirely unpaid amateur occlupanologists such as yourself.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-61\" title=\"taxon_toxo\" src=\"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2012\/02\/taxon_toxo.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"40\" height=\"38\" \/><\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_1125\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2012\/03\/collection_folder.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1125\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-1125\" style=\"border: 0pt none;\" title=\"collection_folder\" src=\"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2012\/03\/collection_folder-300x173.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"173\" srcset=\"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2012\/03\/collection_folder-300x173.jpg 300w, http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2012\/03\/collection_folder-190x110.jpg 190w, http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2012\/03\/collection_folder.jpg 947w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-1125\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">HORG collection holdings<\/p><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"description\">\n<p><strong>Identification Placards<br \/>\n<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-full wp-image-61 alignleft\" title=\"taxon_haplo\" src=\"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2012\/02\/taxon_haplo.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"40\" height=\"38\" \/>The Graphical Outreach team at HORG is proud to offer this free <a href=\"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/05\/horg_collection_page_blank.pdf\">print-your-own set of cut-out identifcation placards<\/a> for the excitable amateur scientists out there who want to start their own collection! Each placard is sized for a standard vinyl 20-count coin pocket page, ready for your own archival grade three-ring binder that you purchase on your own without our help!<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Contact HORG To contact HORG, send a missive to occlupanid @ horg dot com. The Holotypic Occlupanid Research Group is a nonprofit organization dedicated to the study, education, and preservation of a group of inanimate objects that garners little attention in our modern world. Its use in our society is ignored, and its fascinating forms [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":[],"aioseo_notices":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/pages\/1040"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fcomments&post=1040"}],"version-history":[{"count":10,"href":"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\